Step-by-step reasoning:
- The user wants to turn on the Hall Light to 75% brightness.
- The trigger is a physical turn on of the Closet light, which is a COC event with command "Fast On" (DFON) from the Closet light.
- The action is to send the "On" command to Hall Light with parameter 75% (brightness).
- Use the device names and commands exactly as per the DEVICE STRUCTURE.
- The condition checks for COC "DFON" from Closet light.
- The action sends "On" (DON) command to Hall Light with parameter 75%.

{
  "routine": {
    "name": "Turn on Hall Light to 75% when Closet light is physically turned on",
    "condition": {
      "==": {
        "device": "Closet light",
        "coc": "DFON"
      }
    },
    "action": {
      "device": "Hall Light",
      "command": "On",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "",
          "value": 75,
          "uom": "%",
          "precision": 0
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
